JavaScript rest parameters The rest parameter, shown as (...). A rest parameter allows you to represent an indefinite number of arguments as an array.
function fn(a,b,...args) { // ^^^^^^^ rest parameter available as an array of elements for (const a of args){ //do something with a } } rest parameters are available as an array
wrong way to declare a rest parameter function fn(a,...rest,b) { //error }

A user-agent is used to recognize the browser and the device the project, whatismybrowser.com have a database of user agents it&rsquo;s just a string that says about your browser and device type that is sent as a cookie in every request. You can find your current user agent by googling &ldquo;what is my user agent&rdquo;
